$ Shell command: tput
@ tput

{ Print at specific coordinates

  With `cup`, it's possible to `echo` a string at specific coordinates:
  gh|shell-commands|/tput/cup-coordinates.sh||

}
{ Colors #colors

  gh|shell-commands|/tput/colors.sh||

  See also → Linux/shell/ANSI-escape-sequences

}
{ Decorating text

  Text can be decorated with a *bold* or *underlined* attribute:
  gh|shell-commands|/tput/decorate-text.sh||

}

